From: 3090 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-08
Subject: [PATCH] gemma4_mm v0.5.10: per-expert AWQ source format (backport of patch 028)

v0.5.10 sister of patch 028 (which targets v0.5.11 line 714+). Until
the 3090 dev rig env-rebuilds to v0.5.11 we ship two patch files for
the same fix: setup.sh's `git apply --check` silently skips whichever
doesn't match the running source.

Without this patch on v0.5.10: per-expert AWQ keys like
`experts.<E>.<proj>.qweight` (R9700 26B mirror format, post-converter-
fix v3b 21B-REAP format) silently fall through unmatched in
gemma4_mm.py:802+ load_weights — the existing fused-experts mapping
only handles 3D `[num_experts, ...]` tensors. MoE blocks stay at
default-init, server log shows `expert0_first4=[0,0,0,0]` for every
layer, validator returns `(reasoning)` placeholder.

After this patch: per-expert mapping via FusedMoE.make_expert_params_
mapping is checked BEFORE the fused mapping. Validator pre-repack
diagnostic flips from 27/30 layers expert0=zero to 30/30 expert0=non-
zero. (Generation-quality issues beyond MoE loading are tracked
separately — this patch closes the loader gap only.)

